            <span>Worked minutes are calculated by summing all valid
              punch pairs, ensuring that break intervals are excluded
              from productive time.</span></p>
          <div contenteditable="false">
            <hr></div>
          <h3><span>2. mac_ticketno vs ticketno</span></h3>
          <p class="isSelectedEnd"><span>Agreed. The system maps
              biometric data using </span><code dir="ltr"><span>mac_ticketno</span></code><span>
              with </span><code dir="ltr"><span>ticketno</span></code><span>
              through Employee Master, allowing flexibility where both
              differ across mills.</span></p>
          <div contenteditable="false">
            <hr></div>
          <h3><span>3. Night Festival Holiday (NFH) Flag</span></h3>
          <p class="isSelectedEnd"><span>Agreed. NFH eligibility is
              handled as per statutory requirements, and the system
              assigns the appropriate attendance flag based on employee
              eligibility and presence.</span></p>
          <div contenteditable="false">
            <hr></div>
          <h3><span>4. Pr_DattExcept Table (Weekly-Off / Exception
              Handling)</span></h3>
          <p class="isSelectedEnd"><span>Partially aligned. In the
              system, </span><strong><span>Pr_DattExcept</span></strong><span>
              is primarily used for handling:</span></p>
          <ul data-spread="false">
            <li><span>Missing or incomplete punch data</span></li>
            <li><span>Irregular punch scenarios</span></li>
          </ul>
          <p class="isSelectedEnd"><span>Weekly-off working is derived
              through shift configuration and processed accordingly
              (Present/OT) based on setup.</span></p>
          <div contenteditable="false">
            <hr></div>
          <h3><span>5. PostOT_AttnDwnd Flag</span></h3>
          <p class="isSelectedEnd"><span>Agreed. OT calculated during
              attendance download is provisional. Final OT is subject to
              HR verification and can be modified in the Payroll module
              before finalization.</span></p>
          <div contenteditable="false">
            <hr></div>
          <h3><span>6. Attendance Lock (PR_AttendanceOTLock)</span></h3>
          <p class="isSelectedEnd"><span>Agreed. Attendance is locked by
              HR Admin after validation, preventing further
              modifications.</span></p>
          <div contenteditable="false">
            <hr></div>
          <h3><span>7. KSP_AttendanceTransferDate (Stored Procedure)</span></h3>
          <p class="isSelectedEnd"><span>Agreed. This procedure ensures
              consistent day-by-day processing, aligning batch execution
              with transactional logic.</span></p>
          <div contenteditable="false">
            <hr></div>
          <h3><span>8. Actual Shift vs Scheduled Shift (ActShift)</span></h3>
          <p class="isSelectedEnd"><span>Agreed. ActShift is derived
              based on actual punch timings and shift definitions. It is
              system-calculated and not directly captured from the
              biometric device.</span></p>
          <div contenteditable="false">
            <hr></div>
          <h3><span>9. Half-Day Threshold Formula</span></h3>
          <p class="isSelectedEnd"><span>Agreed. Half-day and full-day
              eligibility are configurable in Shift Setup and are
              applied dynamically during attendance processing.</span></p>
          <div contenteditable="false">
            <hr></div>
          <h3><span>10. modifiedon Protection</span></h3>
          <p class="isSelectedEnd"><span>Slight clarification:</span><br>
            <span>During reprocessing, records with </span><strong><span>manual
                modifications (modifiedon is not null)</span></strong><span>
              are </span><strong><span>not overwritten</span></strong><span>
              by the system. This ensures that user-corrected data
              remains intact, while system-generated records can be
              refreshed.</span></p>
          <div contenteditable="false">
            <hr></div>
          <h3><span>Additional Clarification (Important)</span></h3>
          <p class="isSelectedEnd"><span>The attendance download process
              is strictly limited to </span><strong><span>biometric
                data processing</span></strong><span> and is
              system-driven.</span></p>
          <p class="isSelectedEnd"><span>Any manual corrections such as:</span></p>
          <ul data-spread="false">
            <li><span>Attendance status changes</span></li>
            <li><span>OT adjustments</span></li>
            <li><span>Punch corrections</span></li>
          </ul>
          <p class="isSelectedEnd"><span>are performed separately in the
            </span><strong><span>Payroll Daily Attendance Entry </span></strong><span>,
              ensuring proper audit control and data integrity.</span></p>
          <div contenteditable="false">
            <hr></div>
          <p><span>Kindly let us know if any further clarification is
              required.</span></p>
          <p>Thanks &amp; Regards</p>
          <p>M.Sathishkumar</p>
          <div class="moz-cite-prefix">On 09/04/2026 02:48 pm, Palanivel
            wrote:<br>
          </div>
          <blockquote type="cite"
            cite="mid:2e28b1c4-08ff-4a0e-b68e-bab624219989@kalsofte.com">
            <p class="isSelectedEnd"><span>Dear Mr. Sathishkumar,</span></p>
            <p class="isSelectedEnd"><span>Please find below the
                clarifications for the IST Review Questions pertaining
                to the FSD document:</span></p>
            <div contenteditable="false">
              <hr></div>
            <p class="isSelectedEnd"><strong><span>1. Multiple Punches
                  per Shift</span></strong><br>
              <strong><span>Clarification:</span></strong><br>
              <span>Multiple punches (In/Out) are considered to
                accurately capture actual working time excluding break
                periods.</span></p>
            <p class="isSelectedEnd"><strong><span>Example Logic:</span></strong><br>
              <span>Net Worked Time = (OutTime1 − InTime1) + (OutTime2 −
                InTime2)</span><br>
              <span>= 233 + 217 = 450 minutes</span></p>
            <p class="isSelectedEnd"><span>Break Duration = 30 minutes
                (excluded from productive time)</span></p>
            <p class="isSelectedEnd"><span>For a standard shift of 480
                minutes with a 30-minute scheduled break, the expected
                net working time is 450 minutes.</span></p>
            <div contenteditable="false">
              <hr></div>
            <p class="isSelectedEnd"><strong><span>2. mac_ticketno vs
                  ticketno</span></strong><br>
              <strong><span>Clarification:</span></strong><br>
              <span>In most mills, both values are identical. However,
                where differences exist, a </span><strong><span>mapping
                  facility is available in the Employee Master</span></strong><span>
                to link </span><em><span>mac_ticketno</span></em><span>
                with </span><em><span>ticketno</span></em><span>.</span></p>
            <div contenteditable="false">
              <hr></div>
            <p class="isSelectedEnd"><strong><span>3. Night Festival
                  Holiday (NFH) Flag</span></strong><br>
              <strong><span>Clarification:</span></strong><br>
              <span>This is a </span><strong><span>statutory
                  requirement under the Tamil Nadu Shops and
                  Establishments Act</span></strong><span>.</span></p>
            <ul data-spread="false">
              <li><span>If an employee works on NFH → Eligible for one
                  additional day salary (either OT or regular pay as per
                  policy)</span></li>
              <li><span>If absent → Still eligible for NFH salary</span></li>
            </ul>
            <div contenteditable="false">
              <hr></div>
            <p class="isSelectedEnd"><strong><span>4. Pr_DattExcept
                  Table (Weekly-Off Attendance)</span></strong><br>
              <strong><span>Clarification:</span></strong><br>
              <span>Employees who work on weekly off are processed based
                on mill-specific configuration:</span></p>
            <ul data-spread="false">
              <li><span>Either marked as </span><strong><span>Present</span></strong><span>,
                  or</span></li>
              <li><span>Treated as </span><strong><span>Overtime (OT)</span></strong></li>
            </ul>
            <div contenteditable="false">
              <hr></div>
            <p class="isSelectedEnd"><strong><span>5. PostOT_AttnDwnd
                  Flag</span></strong><br>
              <strong><span>Clarification:</span></strong><br>
              <span>OT calculated during attendance download is </span><strong><span>provisional</span></strong><span>.</span></p>
            <p class="isSelectedEnd"><span>HR personnel are responsible
                for:</span></p>
            <ul data-spread="false">
              <li><span>Verification</span></li>
              <li><span>Modification (if required)</span><br>
                <span>based on disciplinary or punch irregularities.</span></li>
            </ul>
            <div contenteditable="false">
              <hr></div>
            <p class="isSelectedEnd"><strong><span>6. Attendance Lock
                  (PR_AttendanceOTLock)</span></strong><br>
              <strong><span>Clarification:</span></strong><br>
              <span>Attendance locking is performed by the </span><strong><span>HR
                  Admin</span></strong><span> after verifying and
                reconciling daily attendance records.</span></p>
            <div contenteditable="false">
              <hr></div>
            <p class="isSelectedEnd"><strong><span>7.
                  KSP_AttendanceTransferDate (Stored Procedure)</span></strong><br>
              <strong><span>Clarification:</span></strong><br>
              <span>This procedure performs </span><strong><span>day-by-day
                  replication of attendance logic</span></strong><span>,
                ensuring consistency with transactional calculations.</span></p>
            <div contenteditable="false">
              <hr></div>
            <p class="isSelectedEnd"><strong><span>8. Actual Shift vs
                  Scheduled Shift (ActShift)</span></strong><br>
              <strong><span>Clarification:</span></strong><br>
              <span>Differences occur when employees work on </span><strong><span>weekly
                  off or non-scheduled days</span></strong><span>.</span></p>
            <ul data-spread="false">
              <li><span>ActShift is </span><strong><span>derived from
                    shift setup</span></strong><span> based on actual
                  In/Out punches</span></li>
              <li><span>It is not directly captured from the biometric
                  device</span></li>
            </ul>
            <div contenteditable="false">
              <hr></div>
            <p class="isSelectedEnd"><strong><span>9. Half-Day Threshold
                  Formula</span></strong><br>
              <strong><span>Clarification:</span></strong><br>
              <span>The half-day and full-day eligibility criteria are </span><strong><span>customer-configurable</span></strong><span>
                within the Shift Setup:</span></p>
            <ul data-spread="false">
              <li><span>“Half Day From”</span></li>
              <li><span>“Full Day From”</span></li>
            </ul>
            <div contenteditable="false">
              <hr></div>
            <p class="isSelectedEnd"><strong><span>10. modifiedon
                  Protection</span></strong><br>
              <strong><span>Clarification:</span></strong><br>
              <span>Manually edited records in </span><strong><span>Pr_Datt</span></strong><span>
                are overwritten during updates; however:</span></p>
            <ul data-spread="false">
              <li><span>All modifications are </span><strong><span>logged
                    within the ERP system</span></strong></li>
              <li><span>Manual correction is performed through the </span><strong><span>attendance
                    correction interface</span></strong></li>
            </ul>
            <div contenteditable="false">
              <hr></div>
            <p class="isSelectedEnd"><span>Kindly review the above
                clarifications and provide your feedback.</span></p>
            <p><span>Thanks &amp; Regards,</span><br>
              <strong><span>V. Palanivel</span></strong></p>
